{
  "stem": "15197.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We lived on the outskirts at that time of Warsaw, very close to the railroad station, which was constantly an object of bombardment.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he want to calm us down, the kids, and he used to start telling us story that he remembers the German.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They are not so terrible.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Oh, Hitler talked this.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Hitler said that.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But he remembers them from World War I.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they were quite pleasant and kind.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And you will see that when they will come in, this is not so terrible.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Before Hitler occupied Warsaw, of course we know.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Before Hitler became the chancellor of Germany.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This was in 1933 he became-- yes.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Poland is a Catholic land.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Antisemitism starts in the church.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the Polish people, and special the simple people, they were constantly-- they have that antisemitism rooted from the childhood.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it was daily occurrences when they said that all you are Zyd or that Zyd was killed Christ.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it was even-- we read in the high schools or in the higher education in the university where Jews were staying not being singled out, not permitted to be the same benches than the other students.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they were-- the pogroms and [NON-ENGLISH] as a child.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I remember there other pogroms which were also very characteristic in Poland.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Polish in-- the Poles in general were the majority antisemitic, and so it was impossible even as a child not to feel or to have the atmosphere-- to feel the atmosphere about this attitude toward Jews.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Before Hitler started his antisemitic propaganda in Germany, but even at that time Poles were the one who picked it up very, very fast.",
      "word_count": 24
    }
  ],
